main event: A UFO was reported in Portland, Oregon on March 6, 1967, but was concluded to have insufficient data for proper evaluation.
interesting points: The object was described as approximately 135 feet long and 65 feet wide., The color of the object was unknown due to darkness, but it reflected colored lights with different hues., The object hovered at about 300 feet altitude for about 30 seconds., After hovering, the object ascended vertically and moved towards a ridge., The weather conditions were clear and there was a nearly full moon during the observation.
witness description: A high school student who was deemed reliable.
